cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with cognitive radio systems, which are primarily related to networking and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization of transmission probabilities, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with cooperative relaying, which is related to security and cryptography (cs.CR) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses multiple access schemes, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
